article.headline: Fairfield 66, CS Northridge 65
article.story: LOS ANGELES (AP) -- Terrence Todd scored 18 points, including the game-winning layup with 4.2 seconds to lead Fairfield past Cal State Northridge 66-65 on Friday. The Matadors (5-5) had a chance to win the game in the closing seconds, but Mike Efevberha dribbled into three Fairfield players and had the ball knocked away as time expired. Efevberha had given Northridge a 65-64 lead with his first field goal of the night, coming with 18 seconds to play. Jonathan Heard led Northridge with a career-best 25 points and 10 rebounds and Calvin Chitwood added 10 points. Fairfield (2-7) was led by DeWitt Maxwell who scored 13 points. The win snapped the Stags' (2-7) three-game losing streak and ended Northridge's seven-game home win streak.
